title: News Wrap: Hurricane Joaquin batters the Bahamas PBS NewsHour
text: In our news wrap Friday, the Bahamas suffered heavy flooding, torrents of rain and howling winds from Hurricane Joaquin. There were no reports of casualties, but the U.S. Coast Guard reported a cargo ship missing with 33 people on board. Also, the September labor report showed employers added just 142,000 jobs, fewer than expected.
